Modular Multithreaded String Pipeline (C11)

## Build & Test

- Build:
  - `./build.sh`
- Run smoke tests:
  - `./test.sh`

## Usage

- Pipeline: `./build/pipeline name1,name2,... < input.txt`
- Example: `echo "Hello World" | ./build/pipeline uppercaser,sink_stdout`

## Plugins

- `logger`: append to `output/pipeline.log`
- `typewriter`: optional per-char delay (see env below)
- `uppercaser`: convert to upper case
- `rotator`: Caesar rotation by N
- `flipper`: reverse string
- `expander`: collapse spaces/tabs, trim edges
- `sink_stdout`: print to stdout, consume end-of-stream

## Env Vars

- `ROTATE_N`: rotation amount for `rotator` (default: 13)
- `TYPEWRITER_DELAY_US`: per-char delay in microseconds for `typewriter` (default: 100000). Tests set this to 1000.

## Build Notes

- macOS (clang): plugins as `.dylib`, rpath `@loader_path/plugins`
- Linux (gcc): plugins as `.so`, rpath `$ORIGIN/plugins`, link with `-ldl`
